<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">STARTING UP A SOLOING-GNOME</b></font> - <small>Grummel, Test Server</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    Memorize and hotkey the 2 spells you have got. Find your guildmaster and get your newbierobe. Spend 5 trainingpoints in piercing.
<p>Head towards steamfont.
Kill decaying skeletons, kobold runts, and giant rats (They all con white/black). 
When a decaying skel holds a weapon he is a good target. But be sure that ur mana nad health is up. The weapon will give you good money. There are only two weapons, which you should keep: one cracked staff and 
one worn great staff. Use them to train 1HB and 2HB. Use your newbie dagger to train piercing. I always keep all three skills maxxed out. 
<p>If you want to sell your loot go to the merchant close to the newbie area (the stone circle) and sell ONLY stuff, which is cheap (4-8 cp) and can't be stacked, because this merchant has bad prizes. For the full sale of your loot go to the merchant in the last hut close to Ak'Anon entrance (when you face the entrance it is the leftmost hut).
<p>When you have collected around 8gp, go back to Ak'Anon and buy a large backback and the spell summon dagger, which will give u a much better piercing weapon for just a gp and some change.
<p> at level 2-3 start killing spiders and deseased rats, too. But you have to be VERY careful, because they gang up on you. So only attack lonley spiders on top of the newbie-valley. I for myself targeted a spider, climbed the zone-edge as far as possible and then used the burn spell. I never had to fight 2 spiders at the same time.
<p> Don't attack any clockworks! they con low-level but fight much better. Wait until you get your pet.
<p> Still your favorite aim will be skeletons and kobold runts, because they may cary valuable items.
<p> When you hit level 4, you get your first pet! You should have more then enough money by this time to buy the earth-elementalkin spell.
 The next to spells are Burn (very important), Gate,  summon bandages (will be VERY important later on), and fire aura. 
Make sure that you bind wounds skill is always maxxed out.
<p> go back to steamfont and summon your fist pet. Yeah! Kill everything in the newbieyone, that you can find (except Bugglepub). There is a kbobld close to the camp, which can be attacked without training the other. Kill it, too.
looting will be your most difficult task now. (There are soooo many corpses now of pet-killed-monsters) 
<p> It shouldn't take long until you reach level 5. Your days in steamfont are over for now. Go on greate faydark (don't forget the mail from the guy at close to the bank-ramp).
Find someone, who will bind you close to the middle Kelethin-elevator. Deliver the mail and you will get some important faction adjustments. (If you want, you can deliver more mail from Felwithe or Ak'Anon to Kelethin)
Now hunt orc pawns and trxie twister and loneley orc centurions. 
<p> Once you are level 6 (i did it allready at level 5, but that is quite tough and you have to know what you are doing) go into crushbone. Don't care about the orcs outside CB. The reasons:
<p> 1. The orcs inside CB have CB belts which you can bring to a guy in Kaladim (basement of the warriorguild) for really good exp.
<p> 2. It is easier to find lonesome orcs inside crushbone then outside
<p> 3. It is easier to find some, who will help you inside CB.
<p> In CB kill the orcs close to the entrance and straight out and west of the entrance. Later on go on to the Slaver are and to the legio huts. But be prepared to run and loose your pet!
So here are some lifesaving hints: If you can't see your pet, move immediateley close to some higher level players, who can help you. If you can't see your pet and you here 'taunting master', RUN and ZONE! True sometime your pet only atracted 1 cent, but most of the time he has a full train on his back and as soon as your pet is dead (2 secs later), the train will chase YOU!
<p> With the help of the CB belt quest you should reach level 12 in no time.
<p> 
<p> Now that you have bind affinity go on to either innoluthe/upper guk for some netted and/or mesh armor or if you have a good group go to paw and try to get a runed totem staff. (or by this somewhere).
<p> Allthoug you can get the insignia rings pretty easaly from the dervs in SRO. Later on (level 15-18) kill crocs in NRO. At level 18 there are many different paths to go. for a party runnyey is nice. Or go to unrest of back to crushbone to hunt down the trainer, the ambassador and the emporer.


    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
